A workshop user would like to create a authentication and access control system that allows them to securely log in and access the corrrct dashboard

*User Acceptance criteria
- User must be able to enter their email and password (this input is required)
- An error message must display if an incorrect inpur it made ( messsage must clear and relay to the user what mistake they have made)
- When the correct details are input the user will be directed to the dashboard (the dashboard displayed must correspond with the login details provided)
- User session must be protected
- Passwrds stored in the database must not be in plain text (being stored as plain text will leave the passwords vulnerable if the data is breached)

